## ğŸ›ï¸ Architecture Patterns

### Handler-Service-Repository Pattern
```go
// Handler layer - HTTP concerns only
type Handler struct {
    service   *Service
    validator *validator.Validate
}

// Service layer - Business logic
type Service struct {
    repo   Repository
    cache  *redis.Client
    logger *slog.Logger
}

// Repository layer - Data access
type Repository interface {
    Create(ctx context.Context, entity *Entity) error
    GetByID(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Entity, error)
    Update(ctx context.Context, id string, entity *Entity) error
    Delete(ctx context.Context, id string) error
}
```

### Dependency Injection
```go
// âœ… GOOD: Constructor-based dependency injection
func NewHandler(service *Service) *Handler {
    return &Handler{
        service:   service,
        validator: validator.New(),
    }
}

func NewService(repo Repository, cache *redis.Client, logger *slog.Logger) *Service {
    return &Service{
        repo:   repo,
        cache:  cache,
        logger: logger,
    }
}
```

